WEBVTT

00:00.734 --> 00:03.001
♪♪

00:03.003 --> 00:06.271
The poor suckers have no idea
what they're being exposed to.

00:06.273 --> 00:08.941
It'd be hilarious
if it wasn't so funny.

00:08.943 --> 00:11.810
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

00:11.812 --> 00:17.416
♪♪

00:17.418 --> 00:22.287
♪♪

00:22.289 --> 00:23.756
[ Drawer closes ]
Morning, Raul.

00:23.758 --> 00:25.958
What? I'm not doing anything.
Hagar wanted me to get a file.

00:25.960 --> 00:27.826
Sounds great.
Have a good one.

00:27.828 --> 00:30.094
[ Sighs ]

00:30.096 --> 00:32.564
♪♪

00:32.566 --> 00:35.300
Hey, Raul.
You get a haircut?

00:35.302 --> 00:36.368
'Cause you look terrific.

00:36.370 --> 00:37.702
Give me the number.

00:37.704 --> 00:39.638
My husband's
always looking for a place.

00:39.640 --> 00:41.906
Yeah, absolutely.

00:41.908 --> 00:44.042
[ Sighs ]

00:44.044 --> 00:51.183
♪♪

00:51.185 --> 00:53.185
Rauuuul...

00:53.187 --> 00:54.453
[ Gasps ]

00:54.455 --> 00:56.321
[ Weakly ]
You forgot to sign...

00:56.323 --> 00:59.591
Keith's birthday card.

00:59.593 --> 01:01.926
♪♪

01:01.928 --> 01:03.195
Okay.

01:03.197 --> 01:07.866
♪♪

01:07.868 --> 01:09.201
Oh.

01:10.004 --> 01:12.070
[ Gasps ]
Morning.

01:12.072 --> 01:13.472
You want me to grab that
for ya?

01:13.474 --> 01:15.207
Uh, it's fine.
The mailbox is right there.

01:15.209 --> 01:17.275
I'll just shove it in.
Right.

01:17.277 --> 01:19.744
Wouldn't it be quicker
for you just to give it to me?

01:19.746 --> 01:21.746
It's kind of sensitive
information. That's all.

01:21.748 --> 01:24.750
Maybe it's something you
shouldn't be mailing, then.

01:25.419 --> 01:28.687
[ Muffled shouting ]

01:28.689 --> 01:35.560
♪♪

01:35.562 --> 01:37.196
Morning.

01:38.899 --> 01:40.899
[ Gunshot ]

01:40.901 --> 01:45.570
♪♪

01:45.572 --> 01:48.240
I'm afraid my parasitic illness
has progressed more rapidly

01:48.242 --> 01:51.043
than doctors anticipated.
[ Sighs ]

01:51.045 --> 01:52.310
Scholls, would you...

01:52.312 --> 01:54.847
Raul Chamgerlain
worked at the offices

01:54.849 --> 01:55.848
of Hagar & Marmaduke

01:55.850 --> 01:57.850
as a law clerk
until he was mailed to death

01:57.852 --> 02:01.453
at 10:25 a.m. yesterday,
just missing the morning pickup.

02:01.455 --> 02:04.789
Let me guess -- Hagar
& Marmaduke represents Veggelon,

02:04.791 --> 02:07.526
the largest industrial-farming
company in America.

02:07.528 --> 02:09.794
Veggelon raised eyebrows
at the EPA

02:09.796 --> 02:11.530
when they released
a new pesticide,

02:11.532 --> 02:13.198
and a study was commissioned.

02:13.200 --> 02:14.667
Once their lawyers
got involved,

02:14.669 --> 02:17.335
all of a sudden,
the study vanished.

02:17.337 --> 02:19.003
Good guess.
That's exactly right.

02:19.005 --> 02:20.539
Let me also guess --

02:20.541 --> 02:22.541
Chamgerlain had
the goods on Veggelon

02:22.543 --> 02:24.342
and was gonna sing
like a canary.

02:24.344 --> 02:25.810
That's also exactly right,

02:25.812 --> 02:28.346
and he missed the concert
because of his death.
Oh.

02:28.348 --> 02:30.482
Charo: I'm the most perceptive
person anyone's ever met,

02:30.484 --> 02:33.351
and I still can't figure out
how this involves us.

02:33.353 --> 02:36.555
Although,
you really dislike Tribeca.

02:36.557 --> 02:38.090
Something happened
between you.

02:38.092 --> 02:39.491
That's ridiculous.

02:39.493 --> 02:40.959
I love Tribeca.

02:40.961 --> 02:42.561
Atkins: [ Gasping ]

02:43.830 --> 02:45.297
[ Grunts ]

02:45.299 --> 02:47.165
Don't you people see?

02:47.167 --> 02:48.367
The government
is powerless

02:48.369 --> 02:50.769
against
these giant corporations.

02:50.771 --> 02:52.370
Sorry. Not powerless.

02:52.372 --> 02:53.638
Paid by.

02:53.640 --> 02:55.840
Veggelon has unleashed
this pesticide

02:55.842 --> 02:57.376
on the town
of Cheyenne, Wyoming,

02:57.378 --> 02:58.977
and in addition
to having to live there,

02:58.979 --> 03:00.913
people are already experiencing
health issues.

03:00.915 --> 03:01.980
But all their complaints

03:01.982 --> 03:03.848
are being squashed
by Veggelon's lawyers.

03:03.850 --> 03:05.918
So we're gonna
take 'em down.

03:05.920 --> 03:08.186
Hagar & Marmaduke, Veggelon,

03:08.188 --> 03:10.054
and maybe a few townspeople

03:10.056 --> 03:11.990
just to let 'em know
we're really serious.

03:11.992 --> 03:13.391
Whoa.

03:13.393 --> 03:15.327
So we're actually fighting
evil people

03:15.329 --> 03:17.262
for the sake
of innocent people.

03:17.264 --> 03:19.264
We're the good guys.

03:19.266 --> 03:23.401
You see, Tribeca, the Special
Division Force is a good force.

03:23.403 --> 03:26.605
It's a force
for truth and justice.

03:26.607 --> 03:29.942
Scholls, pass out
the phony law degrees.

03:29.944 --> 03:32.778
[ Breathes deeply ]

03:34.348 --> 03:35.814
♪♪

03:35.816 --> 03:37.149
Ooh.

03:37.151 --> 03:45.890
♪♪

03:45.892 --> 03:48.092
Man:<i>In this case,</i>
<i> the patient regrew neurons</i>

03:48.094 --> 03:50.162
<i> in the same area,</i>
<i> resulting in...</i>
[ Clears throat ]

03:50.164 --> 03:52.631
<i> ...increased motor function</i>
<i> and tactile sensitivity</i>

03:52.633 --> 03:54.366
<i> that continued to...</i>

03:58.105 --> 03:59.405
[ Door closes ]

04:00.907 --> 04:02.374
[ Door opens ]

04:02.376 --> 04:04.276
[ Door closes ]

04:05.912 --> 04:07.179
[ Loud thud ]

04:07.181 --> 04:09.982
Mm. Mm. Mm.

04:09.984 --> 04:11.183
This just feels wrong.

04:11.185 --> 04:12.450
That's my phone.
Mm.

04:12.452 --> 04:13.718
What about the team?

04:13.720 --> 04:15.387
Don't you think
they're starting to suspect?

04:15.389 --> 04:16.789
Oh, trust me,
they're clueless.

04:16.791 --> 04:19.858
Mm. Mm.
They're so going
to plow-town.

04:20.527 --> 04:21.593
That's my son.

04:21.595 --> 04:26.198
Soon to be your grandson,
am I right?

04:26.200 --> 04:27.800
What about
the age difference?

04:27.802 --> 04:29.201
You're 24. I'm 23.

04:29.203 --> 04:31.470
Yeah, and in 20 years,
we'll both be the same age.

04:31.472 --> 04:33.138
I just know this is
gonna go south somehow.

04:33.140 --> 04:35.207
I'm counting on it.
Mm.

04:35.209 --> 04:36.975
[ Toilet flushes ]

04:39.279 --> 04:41.546
Wait, Murphy,
who's driving?

04:41.548 --> 04:43.816
[ Jazz music plays ]

04:43.818 --> 04:47.019
Ms. Blatt, it is your contention
that the toxic pesticides

04:47.021 --> 04:50.889
used by Veggelon have caused you
grievous and irreparable harm.

04:50.891 --> 04:52.957
Objection.
Objection.

04:52.959 --> 04:54.226
You do not have
to answer that.

04:54.228 --> 04:55.828
I don't?
No, you don't.

04:55.830 --> 04:59.097
Excuse me, honey.
Give Mommy one second, okay?

04:59.099 --> 05:00.765
I'm Conney Sparzner,

05:00.767 --> 05:03.168
and I'll be representing
Ms. Blatt in this case.

05:03.170 --> 05:06.771
I just got my law license after
15 years of being a homemaker.

05:06.773 --> 05:08.973
My husband was laid off
from the deodorant plant,

05:08.975 --> 05:10.775
so I kinda had
to pick up the slack.

05:10.777 --> 05:12.711
We don't need
to know all that.

05:12.713 --> 05:14.979
Again, Ms. Blatt,
you're claiming

05:14.981 --> 05:18.250
that you suffered harm due to
my client's use of pesticides.

05:18.252 --> 05:20.719
And yet,
you seem perfectly fine.

05:20.721 --> 05:23.856
In what way did
these FDA-approved pesticides

05:23.858 --> 05:25.457
cause you
any health issues?

05:25.459 --> 05:28.060
I've been getting
headaches, nose bleeds,

05:28.062 --> 05:30.262
and I've been diagnosed
with high blood pressure.

05:30.264 --> 05:32.330
All of which could be
pre-existing conditions.

05:32.332 --> 05:33.732
Ms. Sparzner, let me give you

05:33.734 --> 05:36.134
your first real-world
experience as a lawyer --

05:36.136 --> 05:38.002
You have no case,
and you're gonna lose.

05:38.004 --> 05:41.139
This is America, where the evil
guys always win at first.

05:41.141 --> 05:43.442
Then I guess I'll see you
later in the story.

05:44.278 --> 05:45.944
We got this.

05:45.946 --> 05:48.881
♪♪

05:53.087 --> 05:54.687
This pesticide is
some pretty nasty business.

05:54.689 --> 05:56.288
It penetrates
the blood-brain barrier

05:56.290 --> 05:58.457
and disrupts
the endocrine system.

05:59.493 --> 06:02.494
It looks pretty innocuous.

06:02.496 --> 06:04.697
How is it at killing pests?
Unbeatable.

06:04.699 --> 06:07.499
Doesn't even compare to the
stuff you can get at the store.

06:07.501 --> 06:09.033
Sir, no.

06:09.035 --> 06:10.369
It'll have no effect
on the parasite.

06:10.371 --> 06:11.636
I got to do something.

06:11.638 --> 06:13.238
It's starting to affect
my work,

06:13.240 --> 06:15.840
and things are starting
to feel very loose inside.

06:15.842 --> 06:17.242
A.J.: Hey, don't worry
about it, Chief.

06:17.244 --> 06:19.043
We've got you covered.
Charo and I go undercover

06:19.045 --> 06:20.845
at Hagar & Marmaduke
this afternoon.

06:20.847 --> 06:22.581
Scholls?
Headed to my new job

06:22.583 --> 06:24.717
at Veggelon's
processing facility.

06:24.719 --> 06:25.784
Tribeca?

06:25.786 --> 06:27.319
I'm gonna go sit
with Dorothy Blatt

06:27.321 --> 06:29.654
and hear her story, but
if I don't get back by 4:00,

06:29.656 --> 06:31.256
I'm gonna have
to pump again.

06:31.258 --> 06:32.991
Oh.
Oh, what? I'm sorry.

06:32.993 --> 06:37.061
Is my making food
for my child offending you?

06:37.063 --> 06:39.264
♪♪

06:39.266 --> 06:42.000
...and after that, we try
a motion for dismissal

06:42.002 --> 06:44.069
on the grounds
of insufficient standing.

06:44.071 --> 06:47.739
And if that doesn't work, we
move to disqualify the evidence.

06:47.741 --> 06:49.874
Any questions?
A.J.: Yeah, I have one.

06:49.876 --> 06:52.076
Can you, uh, explain
the strategy

06:52.078 --> 06:54.879
behind the defense
of Veggelon's pesticide?

06:54.881 --> 06:59.084
That's what we've been doing
for the past hour and a half.

06:59.086 --> 07:01.219
I'm sorry, who are you?

07:01.221 --> 07:04.489
Uh, this is
Morton...

07:04.491 --> 07:05.824
Peppercorn.

07:05.826 --> 07:07.960
He is
one of the new associates.

07:07.962 --> 07:10.028
And who are you?

07:10.030 --> 07:14.099
Sh-- That's, uh,
Marla...Flender.

07:14.101 --> 07:15.900
The other new associate.

07:15.902 --> 07:18.170
I wasn't aware that we brought
on any new associates.

07:18.172 --> 07:19.738
Oh, yeah.
I-It was in the memo.

07:21.108 --> 07:22.841
All right, Flender,

07:22.843 --> 07:24.977
here's everything we have
on the plaintiff, Dorothy Blatt.

07:24.979 --> 07:27.980
Find anything we can use
to discredit her.

07:27.982 --> 07:30.182
Peppercorn,
research these precedents.

07:30.184 --> 07:33.118
Find any support
for getting the evidence tossed.

07:35.121 --> 07:36.789
You're Flender!
You're Peppercorn!

07:36.791 --> 07:38.457
Okay.
Now get to work.

07:38.459 --> 07:44.797
♪♪

07:44.799 --> 07:48.266
After the baby carrots
are pulled from their mothers,

07:48.268 --> 07:49.668
they're brought here.

07:49.670 --> 07:51.069
You see this robot?

07:51.071 --> 07:53.672
It sorts the good carrots
from the bad.

07:53.674 --> 07:55.407
Make sure it stays on.

07:55.409 --> 07:56.608
Think you can handle it?

07:56.610 --> 07:58.477
Seems easy enough.

08:00.014 --> 08:01.146
Whoa!

08:01.148 --> 08:02.414
[ Sizzling ]

08:02.416 --> 08:04.082
You gotta wear these.

08:04.084 --> 08:06.751
Never touch the carrots
with your bare hands.

08:06.753 --> 08:08.353
Now glove up
and get to it.

08:08.355 --> 08:10.823
We have a shipment for the
preschool that leaves at 2:00.

08:10.825 --> 08:12.557
Are you aware of the use

08:12.559 --> 08:15.027
of dangerous pesticides
by Veggelon?

08:15.029 --> 08:18.230
Listen, lady, I just train
people to keep the robot on

08:18.232 --> 08:21.066
and to add dangerous pesticides
to the carrots.

08:22.436 --> 08:26.238
[ Up-tempo music plays ]

08:26.240 --> 08:29.574
[ Chomping ]

08:29.576 --> 08:30.909
Yep, I see it.

08:30.911 --> 08:32.977
That's a parasite,
all right.

08:32.979 --> 08:35.180
Uh, I don't mean to question
your credentials, Dr. Zaius,

08:35.182 --> 08:38.650
but as I remember,
you got your doctorate in Art?

08:38.652 --> 08:40.585
Is the human body
not the world's

08:40.587 --> 08:42.054
most beautiful piece of art?

08:42.056 --> 08:43.188
I guess.

08:43.190 --> 08:45.390
The theory of this treatment
is that the only thing

08:45.392 --> 08:49.862
that can kill a parasite
is a more powerful parasite.

08:49.864 --> 08:53.832
This is an egg salad sandwich
that was made on Monday.

08:54.869 --> 08:57.402
Mm, that doesn't sound
so bad.

08:57.404 --> 08:59.138
Monday 2008.

09:08.749 --> 09:11.349
Okay, now that you've
finished your snack,

09:11.351 --> 09:12.551
let's begin your treatment.

09:12.553 --> 09:15.687
Nurse, the specimen, please.

09:15.689 --> 09:18.690
This is<i>Cymothoa exigua,</i>

09:18.692 --> 09:20.625
the tongue-eating sea louse.

09:20.627 --> 09:22.160
Once we introduce it
into your system,

09:22.162 --> 09:24.897
it will begin consuming
everything inside your body,

09:24.899 --> 09:26.498
hopefully beginning
with your parasite.

09:26.500 --> 09:30.235
After that, it's just a race to
see who dies first -- you or it.

09:30.237 --> 09:33.305
I like my chances.

09:33.307 --> 09:35.941
All right, here we go.

09:37.844 --> 09:40.779
Oh, boy.
That's really on there.

09:40.781 --> 09:42.046
[ Straining ]

09:42.048 --> 09:43.181
All right,
that's not moving.

09:43.183 --> 09:44.649
You want me
to give it a shot?

09:44.651 --> 09:46.585
No, no, no. I got it.
[ Straining ]

09:46.587 --> 09:48.120
I thought I felt it budge.

09:48.122 --> 09:49.121
[ Straining ]

09:49.123 --> 09:51.856
Oh, maybe it opens
the other way.

09:51.858 --> 09:52.991
Nope.
That just tightened it.

09:52.993 --> 09:54.259
Sometimes if you bang it,
then --

09:54.261 --> 09:56.328
No, no, no.
This is coming off.

09:56.330 --> 09:57.596
[ Straining ]

09:57.598 --> 10:01.266
Wow! This just
does not want to budge.

10:01.268 --> 10:03.668
Gah!
My hand's starting to hurt.

10:03.670 --> 10:06.138
Oh, maybe if I use
the other hand.

10:06.140 --> 10:07.539
[ Scoffs ]
That's ridiculous.

10:07.541 --> 10:09.074
I don't have enough strength
in this hand.

10:09.076 --> 10:10.475
Maybe your hands
are sweaty?

10:10.477 --> 10:12.744
Oh, they're very sweaty.
Okay, this is it.

10:12.746 --> 10:14.413
This is the part
where I just pop it off

10:14.415 --> 10:15.547
and everything gets moving.

10:15.549 --> 10:16.748
Here we go.

10:16.750 --> 10:18.550
Haahh!
Gosh darn it!

10:18.552 --> 10:20.352
This thing's on
really tight!

10:20.354 --> 10:21.886
[ Thuds loudly ]

10:21.888 --> 10:25.290
Maybe the key is to...

10:25.292 --> 10:26.491
hit it suddenly!

10:26.493 --> 10:29.161
Baaah! [ Straining ]

10:29.163 --> 10:31.764
I'm making this
more difficult than it is.

10:31.766 --> 10:33.632
Sometimes if you run it
under warm wat--

10:33.634 --> 10:35.300
No, the faucet's
all the way down the hall.

10:35.302 --> 10:37.435
That seems like
a waste of time.

10:37.437 --> 10:42.307
Maybe if I push down on it
and then turn it...

10:42.309 --> 10:43.642
Hey! Looky there!

10:43.644 --> 10:44.909
Now we know how to do it.

10:44.911 --> 10:47.712
So, it's push down and...

10:47.714 --> 10:49.314
now it's not moving again.

10:49.316 --> 10:51.150
♪♪

10:55.189 --> 10:56.254
♪♪

10:56.256 --> 10:57.656
Charo, check it out.

10:57.658 --> 10:59.391
Dorothy Blatt
is a total fraud.

10:59.393 --> 11:00.725
Take a look.

11:00.727 --> 11:02.727
She's been involved
in over 200 lawsuits.

11:02.729 --> 11:04.129
She sued Crest Whitestrips

11:04.131 --> 11:05.864
because they made
her teeth too white.

11:05.866 --> 11:08.066
She sued Subway because
the stores were above ground.

11:08.068 --> 11:10.202
And she sued Folgers because
it wasn't the best part

11:10.204 --> 11:12.737
of waking up.
Jesus. 5 aliases,
10 years in jail...

11:12.739 --> 11:14.139
Yeah, and take a look
at her rap sheet.

11:14.141 --> 11:16.140
What? She tried to rhyme
"miracle" with "spiritual"?

11:16.142 --> 11:17.942
That's whack.
No. I'm no lawyer,

11:17.944 --> 11:19.944
but I think this makes her
a vexatious litigant.

11:19.946 --> 11:21.346
Which means
that my mother's

11:21.348 --> 11:22.815
fighting on
the wrong side. Again.

11:22.817 --> 11:24.216
She's gonna lose her mind.

11:24.218 --> 11:25.884
Exactly. That's why
we can't tell her.

11:25.886 --> 11:27.285
What? What are
you talking about?

11:27.287 --> 11:28.353
That's my mother.

11:28.355 --> 11:29.754
You don't hatch
from someone's egg

11:29.756 --> 11:30.823
and then keep secrets.
What?

11:30.825 --> 11:32.157
If she finds out
that Blatt's a fraud,

11:32.159 --> 11:34.226
she'll drop the case,
and Veggelon will win.

11:34.228 --> 11:36.561
Is that what you want?
No, but if they didn't do
anything wrong...

11:36.563 --> 11:39.031
You saw the labs.
That stuff is poison.

11:39.033 --> 11:41.366
You mom has to be on her game
and win this case.

11:41.368 --> 11:43.768
Do you remember what happened
the last time she lost it?

11:43.770 --> 11:45.704
She sent me away
to boarding school. I was 2.

11:45.706 --> 11:47.840
Yeah, and how did that
make you feel?

11:47.842 --> 11:49.842
The older kids
used to make fun of me

11:49.844 --> 11:51.109
'cause my skull
hadn't closed.

11:51.111 --> 11:53.378
Veggelon has to lose
this case.

11:53.380 --> 11:54.847
You understand?

11:54.849 --> 11:57.649
-I mean, I guess --
-They have to lose, okay?!

11:57.651 --> 11:59.384
Okay, okay.

11:59.386 --> 12:01.319
[ Breathes deeply ]

12:01.321 --> 12:03.055
Good boy.

12:03.057 --> 12:10.128
♪♪

12:10.130 --> 12:12.664
Your Honor, in light
of recent new evidence,

12:12.666 --> 12:13.866
we would like to ask
that the case

12:13.868 --> 12:16.134
of Blatt v. Veggelon
be dismissed.

12:16.136 --> 12:17.936
And what new evidence
is that?

12:17.938 --> 12:19.337
That you guys
are pure evil?

12:19.339 --> 12:22.675
Order! Order! Order!

12:22.677 --> 12:25.944
I'd like that medium rare.
Thank you.

12:25.946 --> 12:27.612
Mr. Hagar, on what grounds

12:27.614 --> 12:29.147
should I be dismissing
this lawsuit?

12:29.149 --> 12:30.549
Exhibit A.

12:30.551 --> 12:31.950
Neanderthal man.

12:31.952 --> 12:34.152
And this is a record
of Dorothy Blatt's visit

12:34.154 --> 12:35.620
to a doctor
three years ago,

12:35.622 --> 12:39.357
long before any exposure to
Veggelon's delicious pesticide.

12:39.359 --> 12:41.093
And, as you can see,

12:41.095 --> 12:42.695
the doctor has listed
as symptoms --

12:42.697 --> 12:46.030
headaches, nose bleeds,
and high blood pressure.

12:46.032 --> 12:49.634
Pre-existing conditions.
[ Piano plays ]

12:49.636 --> 12:50.969
Wait a second.

12:52.373 --> 12:53.838
This isn't a medical record.

12:53.840 --> 12:56.841
This is a blank job application
for Best Buy.

12:56.843 --> 13:00.245
Damn it. She's got us.
Veggelon is ruined.

13:00.247 --> 13:02.581
Make that check out
to "Fraud Squad, LLC."

13:02.583 --> 13:04.182
That's the name
of my loan-out company.

13:04.184 --> 13:06.518
This isn't right.
What are you doing?

13:06.520 --> 13:09.121
I'm not gonna stand by and let
an innocent gigantic corporation

13:09.123 --> 13:11.990
get trampled by
a single middle-aged woman.

13:11.992 --> 13:15.059
Your Honor, I submit
that Dorothy Blatt,

13:15.061 --> 13:19.531
a.k.a. Dorothy Blart,
a.k.a. Mrs. Stephen Blart,

13:19.533 --> 13:24.136
a.k.a. Mrs. Stephen Conway,
a.k.a. Stephen Conway,

13:24.138 --> 13:28.206
a.k.a.
Inmate Number 8675309,

13:28.208 --> 13:31.543
has been the plaintiff
in over 200 lawsuits,

13:31.545 --> 13:33.678
none of which
have any merit.

13:33.680 --> 13:35.814
Her real name
should be Sue Happy.

13:35.816 --> 13:38.083
I remember you.

13:38.085 --> 13:41.686
You sued Grape Nuts for being
neither grapes nor nuts.

13:41.688 --> 13:43.021
Well, what the hell
are they?!

13:43.023 --> 13:45.023
Gravel-tastin'
mutant cereal.

13:45.025 --> 13:46.625
It is the opinion
of this court

13:46.627 --> 13:49.093
that the case
of Blatt v. Veggelon be dis--

13:49.095 --> 13:50.228
Tribeca:
Objection, Your Honor!

13:50.230 --> 13:52.497
Permission to speak
to opposing counsel.

13:52.499 --> 13:53.698
Flender, is it?

13:53.700 --> 13:55.700
Oh, my God.

13:55.702 --> 13:58.170
That's Flender.
That's Peppercorn.

13:58.172 --> 14:01.706
Sure. I'll see
where you're going with this.

14:01.708 --> 14:03.308
Oh, you're going over there.

14:03.310 --> 14:05.510
Ow!
Why are you tanking my case?

14:05.512 --> 14:06.845
We gotta take
these guys down.

14:06.847 --> 14:08.580
Your client is a fraud, Mama.

14:08.582 --> 14:10.048
A criminal.

14:10.050 --> 14:12.517
Yeah, well, you know
who else was a criminal? Me.

14:12.519 --> 14:13.918
20 years' worth.

14:13.920 --> 14:14.987
Just because this woman
had made a mistake

14:14.989 --> 14:16.921
doesn't mean
she's not entitled to justice.

14:16.923 --> 14:18.857
This isn't justice.
So, I guess...

14:22.329 --> 14:23.528
It's on.

14:23.530 --> 14:24.797
It's on, all right.

14:26.200 --> 14:29.133
Your Honor, in spite of
everything that was just said --

14:29.135 --> 14:32.337
no need to relive it --
I move not to dismiss the case,

14:32.339 --> 14:36.741
but to continue it
under Statute...21-C?

14:36.743 --> 14:39.411
Of Wyoming Civil Code?

14:39.413 --> 14:41.279
Continuance granted.

14:41.281 --> 14:42.881
This court is in recess.

14:42.883 --> 14:46.719
[ Children shouting playfully ]

14:51.225 --> 14:52.557
♪♪

14:52.559 --> 14:55.560
Have you two
lost your minds?!

14:55.562 --> 14:56.628
Sorry, I'm on edge.

14:56.630 --> 14:59.698
I have
an insatiable snail

14:59.700 --> 15:02.768
eating every calorie
I take into my body.

15:03.504 --> 15:06.571
[ Breathes deeply ]

15:06.573 --> 15:08.306
This woman has a case.

15:08.308 --> 15:10.709
It doesn't matter
who she was before.

15:10.711 --> 15:12.911
The company
has abused the law

15:12.913 --> 15:14.646
and abused the rights
of our citizens.

15:14.648 --> 15:16.314
Isn't that
what we're fighting for?

15:16.316 --> 15:17.449
-No.
-No. No!

15:17.451 --> 15:19.584
That's not exactly it.
Look, it's Dorothy Blatt,

15:19.586 --> 15:22.320
or whatever her name is,
that's abusing the law here.

15:22.322 --> 15:24.322
Law! Law! Law!

15:24.324 --> 15:26.591
What part
of "outside the law"

15:26.593 --> 15:30.328
or "beyond the scope of normal
law enforcement" don't you get?

15:30.330 --> 15:34.999
We're a<i>Special</i>Division Force,
not a Division Force.

15:35.001 --> 15:38.403
The Vice President has lost
interest in this case,

15:38.405 --> 15:39.938
and, therefore, so have we.

15:39.940 --> 15:42.741
The company killed a man
for what he knew!

15:42.743 --> 15:45.744
Companies kill people!

15:45.746 --> 15:47.212
That's capitalism.

15:48.348 --> 15:49.948
What are we, huh?

15:49.950 --> 15:52.217
We just take
and drop cases

15:52.219 --> 15:54.619
as it suits
the Vice President's whims?

15:54.621 --> 15:56.288
I spent 20 years in prison,

15:56.290 --> 15:58.791
and this is
what the world is now?

16:00.561 --> 16:03.428
Scholls?

16:03.430 --> 16:05.698
You and I haven't
always seen eye-to-eye,

16:05.700 --> 16:08.433
but you know
what this company is doing.

16:08.435 --> 16:12.304
You've seen
their carrots up close.

16:12.306 --> 16:16.508
Those defenseless,
little baby carrots.

16:16.510 --> 16:19.644
I had a baby once.

16:19.646 --> 16:23.448
And I loved him more
than I've ever loved anything.

16:23.450 --> 16:25.517
And then I found out
that he was your baby.

16:25.519 --> 16:27.586
And you took him from me,
and you sent him away

16:27.588 --> 16:31.189
without even asking me
if I wanted to take care of him.

16:31.191 --> 16:34.593
And now that baby's
all grown up, and he's back.

16:34.595 --> 16:36.729
But he's still all yours.

16:36.731 --> 16:40.132
And I come to work here every
day with my heart torn in half.

16:40.134 --> 16:43.067
And I don't say a word
about it.

16:43.069 --> 16:45.604
That's what I've become.

16:45.606 --> 16:47.439
That's the world now.

16:49.876 --> 16:52.344
[ Voice breaking ]
I didn't know.

16:53.347 --> 16:55.347
Okay, can we get back
to my thing now?

16:56.483 --> 16:58.416
Time to go, Tribeca.

16:58.418 --> 17:00.084
We're moving out.

17:00.086 --> 17:02.354
I'm not going anywhere.

17:02.356 --> 17:05.490
Let justice be done
though the heavens fall.

17:05.492 --> 17:07.092
This lawsuit is garbage.

17:07.094 --> 17:09.294
I'm dismissing it
immediately.

17:09.296 --> 17:11.563
Yeah! Whoo!

17:11.565 --> 17:19.904
♪♪

17:19.906 --> 17:24.042
[ Horses neighing ]

17:24.044 --> 17:25.243
This view taken?

17:25.245 --> 17:28.446
Nah.
There's plenty to go around.

17:28.448 --> 17:29.848
Whiskey?

17:29.850 --> 17:31.650
Yeah, if you're drinking.

17:31.652 --> 17:34.118
♪♪

17:34.120 --> 17:36.254
[ Sighs ]

17:36.256 --> 17:38.390
Looks like I lost my case.

17:38.392 --> 17:40.859
Looks that way.

17:40.861 --> 17:42.527
Felt good for a second.

17:42.529 --> 17:43.796
You know?

17:43.798 --> 17:46.130
Fighting
for innocent people,

17:46.132 --> 17:48.467
going up against the bully.

17:48.469 --> 17:51.536
♪♪

17:51.538 --> 17:55.340
I was thinking about what
you said about the world now.

17:55.342 --> 17:59.744
And I know A.J.'s not my son,
but he was once,

17:59.746 --> 18:02.347
and this is the world
he's gonna inherit.

18:02.349 --> 18:04.683
And maybe it can be
better than this.

18:04.685 --> 18:06.618
Not with me as its lawyer.

18:06.620 --> 18:10.288
Maybe you just need
a little expert advice.

18:10.290 --> 18:15.760
Tribeca, this is my uncle,
Leonard Scholls.

18:15.762 --> 18:17.896
Nice to meet you.

18:17.898 --> 18:20.432
[ Breathes deeply ]

18:20.434 --> 18:23.301
Beautiful night.

18:23.303 --> 18:24.903
Whiskey?

18:24.905 --> 18:26.839
I brought my own.

18:29.109 --> 18:33.045
You know, I did
a little lawyering myself

18:33.047 --> 18:34.446
back in my day.

18:34.448 --> 18:38.316
You ever hear of Brown
vs. the Board of Education?

18:38.318 --> 18:39.651
Yeah.

18:39.653 --> 18:41.854
Well, I lost that one,

18:41.856 --> 18:45.590
but I did pick up
a few things along the way.

18:45.592 --> 18:47.192
Oh, yeah?

18:47.194 --> 18:50.262
You need
a class-action suit.

18:50.264 --> 18:51.463
No.

18:51.465 --> 18:53.198
They can tie that up
for years.

18:53.200 --> 18:54.867
They have the money
and the manpower.

18:54.869 --> 18:57.269
Not if you can convince
the majority of your plaintiffs

18:57.271 --> 19:00.805
to opt
for binding arbitration.

19:00.807 --> 19:02.674
Binding arbitration?
Mm-hmm.

19:02.676 --> 19:05.009
That's it. Then the court
has to hear it immediately.

19:05.011 --> 19:07.345
That's the exact solution
from "Erin Brockovich."

19:07.347 --> 19:09.147
Uncle Leonard,
you're a genius.

19:09.149 --> 19:11.283
Yeah, well,
Earl Warren didn't think so,

19:11.285 --> 19:14.018
but I appreciate
the thought.

19:14.020 --> 19:15.754
♪♪

19:15.756 --> 19:18.490
[ Indistinct conversations ]

19:18.492 --> 19:28.500
♪♪

19:28.502 --> 19:38.176
♪♪

19:38.178 --> 19:40.445
Yes, Mr. Vice President.

19:40.447 --> 19:43.115
Okay. Joe.

19:43.117 --> 19:45.984
Everything went
exactly according to plan.

19:45.986 --> 19:48.787
Charo played them
like a Stradivarius.

19:48.789 --> 19:51.123
It's a kind of violin.

19:51.125 --> 19:53.458
Veggelon's going to be bankrupt
after this,

19:53.460 --> 19:56.528
leaving all of Wyoming open
for French development.

19:56.530 --> 19:59.264
I told some cockamamie story
about missing my baby,

19:59.266 --> 20:01.466
and they ate it up.

20:01.468 --> 20:02.935
Okay, sweetheart.

20:02.937 --> 20:05.337
I love you.

20:05.339 --> 20:07.606
No,<i>you</i>hang up fir--
[ Click ]

20:07.608 --> 20:09.073
Oh.

20:09.075 --> 20:11.143
You did.

20:18.152 --> 20:25.557
♪♪

20:25.559 --> 20:33.431
♪♪

20:33.433 --> 20:41.006
♪♪
